62.3	John_Battelle	John Battelle	John Linwood Battelle (born November 4, 1965) is an entrepreneur, author and journalist. Best known for his work creating media properties, Battelle helped launch Wired in the 1990s and launched The Industry Standard during the dot-com boom. In 2005, he founded the online advertising network Federated Media Publishing, which now ranks as one of the top properties on the Web.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/96/John_Battelle%2C_Web_2.0_Conference.jpg/220px-John_Battelle%2C_Web_2.0_Conference.jpg
